        "title": "Cost breakdown — what drove the increase",
        "body": "Three drivers account for ~90% of the QoQ cost increase: (1) aluminum spot price up 18% in August, (2) unplanned downtime on Line 3 in week 11 (heat exchanger failure), and (3) higher overtime hours to recover the Line 3 backlog. Energy cost rose with a summer peak-pricing tier; this is partially reversible in Q4."
      },
